-- Germany Leads 10-Man Australia 4-0 in Soccer World Cup in South Africa
-- James Cone
-- 2010-06-13T19:57:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-13/germany-leads-10-man-australia-4-0-in-soccer-world-cup-in-south-africa.html

          
          
             Germany leads 10-man Australia 4-0
in their soccer World Cup Group D match today in Durban, South
Africa after 70 minutes.  
 Lukas Podolski got the opening goal in the eighth minute,
with Miroslav Klose doubling the three-time champion’s advantage
on 26 minutes. Thomas Muller scored after 68 minutes, with Cacau
netting the fourth.  
 Australia’s Tim Cahill received a straight red card after
56 minutes for a foul on Bastian Schweinsteiger.   
 Ghana beat Serbia 1-0 in the group’s other opening game
today. Slovenia tops Group C following a 1-0 win against
Algeria.  
          
          


  


        